2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper deals with predicting the efficiency of artists in rendering visual effects in film shots, which involves analyzing and processing visual data. Hence, cs.CV is a likely sub-category.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes machine learning models to solve a complex task in an organization. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI a likely sub-category.
4. cs.GR (Graphics): The paper deals with visual effects in film shots, which involves creating and manipulating graphics. Hence, cs.GR is a possible sub-category.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with visual effects in film shots, which is a form of multimedia. Hence, cs.MM is a possible sub-category.
